  plantName: Daisy
  description: "A daisy is a composite flower (genera Bellis or Chrysanthemum) featuring
    white petals, a yellow center, and the ability to close at night, often symbolizing
    innocence, purity, true love, and new beginnings. Originating from the Old English
    \"d\xE6geseage\" (day's eye), it is also used colloquially to describe a first-rate
    person or thing."
